#: ../../../reference/random/bit_generators/generated/numpy.random.SeedSequence.rst:2
msgid "numpy.random.SeedSequence"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:2
msgid ""
"SeedSequence mixes sources of entropy in a reproducible way to set the "
"initial state for independent and very probably non-overlapping "
"BitGenerators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:6
msgid ""
"Once the SeedSequence is instantiated, you can call the `generate_state` "
"method to get an appropriately sized seed. Calling `spawn(n) <spawn>` will "
"create ``n`` SeedSequences that can be used to seed independent "
"BitGenerators, i.e. for different threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:15
#: numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:59
msgid "**entropy**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:-1
msgid "{None, int, sequence[int]}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:14
msgid ""
"The entropy for creating a `SeedSequence`. All integer values must be non-"
"negative."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:21
#: numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:71
msgid "**spawn_key**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:-1
msgid "{(), sequence[int]}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:18
msgid ""
"An additional source of entropy based on the position of this `SeedSequence` "
"in the tree of such objects created with the `SeedSequence.spawn` method. "
"Typically, only `SeedSequence.spawn` will set this, and users will not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:27
#: numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:68
msgid "**pool_size**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:-1
msgid "{int}, optional"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:24
msgid ""
"Size of the pooled entropy to store. Default is 4 to give a 128-bit entropy "
"pool. 8 (for 256 bits) is another reasonable choice if working with larger "
"PRNGs, but there is very little to be gained by selecting another value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:39
#: numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:62
msgid "**n_children_spawned**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:30
msgid ""
"The number of children already spawned. Only pass this if reconstructing a "
"`SeedSequence` from a serialized form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:42
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random.bit_generator.SeedSequence:43
msgid ""
"Best practice for achieving reproducible bit streams is to use the default "
"``None`` for the initial entropy, and then use `SeedSequence.entropy` to log/"
"pickle the `entropy` for reproducibility:"
msgstr ""

